-----One of the important question.
There are two solutions for this question. 1. Brute Force 2. Optimize
1. Brute force Solution: If we sort the array of string, it'll sort the the string alphabetically. So we can compare first and last string's charecters. If it matches then we will store the characteer.


-------- I've used this code and it works:
var longestCommonPrefix = function(strs) {
    let res = "";
    let minLength = strs[0].length;
    let srt = strs[0];
    for (let i=1; i<strs.length; i++){
        if(strs[i].length < minLength){
            srt = strs[i]; 
            minLength = strs[i].length;
        }
    }
    
    for(let j=0; j<minLength; j++){
        let char = srt[j];
        for(let k=0; k<strs.length; k++){
            if(char!==strs[k][j]){
                return res;
            }
        }
        res+=char;
    }
    return res;
};
